The President and his team met with CEOs from various tech companies to discuss intelligence, technology, and privacy issues. The President updated the CEOs on the progress of implementing reforms announced on January 17, including a new Presidential Directive governing intelligence activities. The President reiterated his commitment to protecting people's rights while ensuring national security. The CEOs were also updated on a comprehensive "big data" review being led by John Podesta, which examines the impact of big data on various aspects of society. Attendees included executives from Netflix, Dropbox, Palantir, Box, Google, and Facebook, along with members of the Administration such as the Secretary of Commerce, Senior Advisor, Counselor, and others.